summary: I think the drill was to get BTS the fck off that stage after the performance so that if anyone collapses/overheats, it'll be...
question: I think the drill was to get BTS the fck off that stage after the performance so that if anyone collapses/overheats, it'll be behind closed curtains. U can see guards waiting for them with water, prepared to assist them to the backstage area. It was BTS's job to get to the backstage for any needed assistance for the next part of the show. & if u talk about care, all the fancams so far show only jm checking up on jk when he was also obviously tired. they're all tired for fuck's sake. I'm so++
answer:
++mad with twitter right now. The audacity for those people to spam twitter with comments about Jimin been ‘coldhearted’ when it’s simply just not true :((

2nd anon: I don’t even get how anyone could term jm of all people “evil” when he’s such a caring dude. To the members, to others but esp to the members. He waits for people, he notices if something is off and is one of the first people to respond. Like he was the same guy who alerted a security guard that a fan was about to faint at their concert. So yeah no

3rd anon: Oh god… there’s literally a pic of them when they were leaving and Jimin is walking by Jungkook’s side… istg people love to shit on Jikook for any stupid reason

____

To sum up:

1. BH is not trustworthy

2. The boys need to rest

3. Jimin is not JK’s nurse

4. Jimin took care of JK anyway (as many fancams show) because he is an angel

5. We will have the same conversation again in 1 month because people never learn
